<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-04-29T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-04-29T11:00:00-05:00" n="573" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d573">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">767.68119/901: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Yugoslavia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Belgrade</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-04-29T17:00:00+01:00">April 29, 1936—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received April 29—2:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>16. Foreign Office yesterday handed note to Turkish Minister here stating
                            that although not a signatory to Straits Convention Yugoslav Government
                            was prepared to second Turkish demand for new agreement.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>